{"word":"ἔμβασις","slug":"ἔμβασις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔμβασις</b></el> <el>(ἔμβᾰσις, εως) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐμβαίνω'><el>ἐμβαίνω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>that on which one goes</i> or <i>steps</i>, <el>ἔμβασις ποδός</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>a shoe</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the foot, hoof</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a bath</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}